# Step 1: Terraform and Azure CLI Setup

## Description
Install and configure Terraform and Azure CLI to begin provisioning Azure infrastructure using Infrastructure-as-Code.

---

## Instructions

### 1. Install Terraform
Download and install Terraform from the official site:
ðŸ‘‰ https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/downloads

Verify installation:

terraform -version


### 2. Install Azure CLI
Follow instructions here:
ðŸ‘‰ https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/install-azure-cli

Verify installation:

az version


### 3. Authenticate with Azure
Login to your Azure account:

az login


Set your default subscription (if needed):

az account set --subscription "<your-subscription-id>"


### 4. Create a Terraform Working Directory

mkdir cloudpos-infra
cd cloudpos-infra


### 5. Initialize Terraform
Create a basic `main.tf` file:

terraform {
  required_providers {
    azurerm = {
      source  = "hashicorp/azurerm"
      version = "~> 3.0"
    }
  }

  required_version = ">= 1.0"
}

provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}


Initialize Terraform:

terraform init


---

